value.value: A response indicating that staging was determined at least in part by imaging.
A question about whether a beam-shaping block was used.

label.value: Breath Control Used as Part of Treatment

value.value: A question about whether a method of controlling the breathing of a patient was used as part of a treatment.

label.value: Diagnostic Imaging Used for M Staging

value.value: A question pertaining to what diagnostic imaging modality was used to determine the staging of distant metastases.

label.value: Diagnostic Imaging Used for N Staging

value.value: A question pertaining to what diagnostic imaging modality was used to determine the staging of regional lymph node involvement.

label.value: Diagnostic Imaging Used for T Staging

value.value: A question pertaining to what diagnostic imaging modality was used to determine the staging of the primary tumor.
A question about which method was used to deliver the treatment plan dose.

A question about which medium was used to calibrate the treatment device or treatment planning system. The numerical values of dose (energy per unit mass) delivered corresponds to either water or muscle, with the former being most common.

An approach to modeling a protein structure based on an initial sequence alignment to a protein with a known 3D structure.  After evaluating and resolving structural irregularities in the initial model, it may be further refined using energy minimization and other procedures.

label.value: Fiducial Markers Used for Image Guidance

value.value: A question about whether fiducial markers were used to support localization during image-guided radiation therapy.

label.value: Has Ever Been in a Clinical Trial

value.value: A question about whether the patient was ever in a clinical trial.

label.value: Heterogeneity Correction Used in Dose Calculation

value.value: A question about whether there were differences in the tissue densities, as reflected in the Hounsfield unit (HU) values measured from the computed tomography images, used in the dose calculation to account for the impact on treatment beams.

label.value: How Likely is Death Related to Treatment

value.value: A question about the likelihood of a patient's death being related to the treatments delivered.

A question about whether the planning performed was robust with optimization to the clinical target volume (CTV) or the planning target volume (PTV) in terms of positional uncertainty and range uncertainty.

label.value: Imaging Captured to Calculate Treatment Session Dose and Compare to Original Plan

value.value: A question about whether imaging captured as part of treatment session was used to calculate dose for that session and compared to the original plan in order to determine if there were changes indicating a need to re-plan and perhaps re-scan.
A question about whether an interpreter was present during an encounter.

label.value: Intervention Performed Prior to Radiation Therapy

value.value: A question about whether an intervention was performed prior to radiation therapy.

A question about whether the plan or plan sum represents all plans treated in the radiation therapy course. If more than one plan is delivered in the course (e.g. spatially separated target volumes for lung metastases and spine metastases or first course and boost), then the course cumulative plan would be a plan sum.

A question about whether the plan or plan sum represents all plans treated in a single phase. All plans in a phase treated the same targets to the same dose per fraction, using the same modality and technique. Multiple plans for a single phase occur with plan revisions (e.g. re-drawing target volumes ) or with the use of technologies enabling per session adaptation. If more than one plan is used in the phase, then this would correspond to a plan sum.
The methods and tools used for DNA analysis and manipulation.
A question about what language used by the patient during the encounter.

A question about which underlying method for the summation of multiple plans was used. The cumulative dose may reflect the intended dose (planning CTs only) or the actual delivered dose based on dose calculations from CTs acquired at each of the treatment sessions.

label.value: Planned Dose is Sum of Other Plan Doses

value.value: A question about whether the dose associated with the plan is created by summing doses from other plans.

label.value: Prescription Specifies Dose Objectives For Single Course

value.value: A question about whether the prescription specifies dose objectives only for a single course. One or more phases may be used in treating a course of radiation therapy. There may only be one course cumulative prescription per radiation therapy course.

label.value: Prescription Specifies Dose Objectives For Single Phase

value.value: A question about whether the prescription specifies dose objectives only for a single phase. A phase is a set of one or more plans treating the same set of target volumes, with the same dose per fraction using the same modality and technique. For example, a phase prescription is a grouping concept a set of distinct treatment plans used in adaptive therapy.

label.value: Prescription Specifies Dose Objectives For Single Treatment Plan

value.value: A question about whether the prescription specifies dose objectives only for a single treatment plan. A phase may be made up of one or more treatment plans. A course may be made up of one or more phases.

label.value: Primary ICD Codes When Treating Secondary

value.value: A question about which ICD codes represent the primary diagnosis when treating the patient for a secondary (metastatic) disease, this is a reference back to the primary diagnosis.
For a rigid or deformable registration, what were the primary structures used to bias the registration?
A question about whether the patient previously underwent active surveillance.
A question about the primary source material used to identify dose contributions from prior radiation treatments.
Techniques based on the principles of physical and chemical science, for the study of biological problems.

label.value: Quantitative Dose Calculations Performed to Evaluate Cumulative Doses

value.value: A question about whether if the course involves reirradiation of overlapping areas, the quantitative dose calculations were carried out to evaluate cumulative doses to inform decisions for the present course of therapy.

label.value: Radiation Field for Current Course Overlaps with Prior Courses

value.value: A question about whether the radiation field for the current course overlaps with radiation fields from prior courses of therapy.
A question about whether a radiation therapy technique known as repainting was used.
A question about whether a beam filter was used to increase in the radiation dose within the planned target volume.
A question about whether a spacer device was used in treatment. Spacers are used to provide protective physical distancing between the tissue being targeted by treatment and any organ(s) at risk.

label.value: Structure Type is Target Structure or Organ at Risk

value.value: A question about whether the structure is a target structure (planning target volume (PTV), clinical target volume (CTV), gross tumor target volume (GTV)), or an organ at risk.
A question about whether technology monitoring changes were used in the imaging of patient surface to detect motion and check alignment.
A question about how the treatment plan was created, i.e., manually or with automated planning tools.
A question about whether the patient was alive or dead on the date of last contact.
A question about which breath control methods that limit or enable triggering on motion resulting from breathing were used during treatment.

label.value: Subcommittee to Evaluate the National Cancer Program

value.value: The frequency with which systemic therapy is administered.
A branch of cardiology concerned with the use of intravascular therapies, including coronary angioplasty and stenting, to treat disorders of the cardiovascular system.
Internal radiation treatment that targets a cancerous tissue with low doses of radiation through the use of permanent implants.
A type of brachytherapy that involves the temporary placement of a radioactive source to deliver radiation over an extended period of time.
A character or string that represents the question of a patient-reported outcome measure.
The physical bearing of the body during blood pressure measurement.
A fiducial marker consisting of implanted carbon seeds.
An implanted metallic coil that is used as a surrogate fiducial marker.
